
All Carma tinderbox builds are defined in carma.buildcf.  New builds should
be defined in this file in the BUILDS hash table.
 
 To run on a client:

 ./build_shellscript --buildcf ./carma.buildcf 
                     --build <full, incremental, tools>
		     --tree carma
		     --mail-each-phase 

 To install a new tinderbox client:

 * Get the tinderbox tarball from cvs.mmarray.org:/sw/carma_pkg.unused
   and unpack into /usr/local/tinderbox or wherever desired.

 * Put the files in this directory in /usr/local/tinderbox/local_conf
   and edit carma.buildcf, tools.sh, and the top of tinderbox.rc to reflect
   local configuration.

 $ cp tinderbox.rc /etc/init.d/tinderbox && chkconfig --add tinderbox
 $ /etc/init.d/tinderbox start  # or reboot

   

Questions?  andy@ovro.caltech.edu, krauch@ovro.caltech.edu.
